1️⃣ Idempotency — Prevent Double Transfer
❓ Problem

User clicks Transfer button twice OR network retry happens.

Without protection:

Money debited twice ❌

Duplicate transactions ❌

✅ Solution: Idempotency Key

Every transfer request must contain unique requestId.

Example:

{
  "fromAccount": 101,
  "toAccount": 202,
  "amount": 500,
  "requestId": "abc123"
}

🔄 Flow

Check if requestId already exists

If exists → return previous result (NO re-processing)

If not → process transfer

Save requestId in DB

DB Table
idempotency_table
-----------------
request_id (PK)
status
response
created_at

Spring Boot Logic (Pseudo)
@Transactional
public TransferResponse transfer(TransferRequest req) {

    if(idempotencyRepo.exists(req.getRequestId())) {
        return idempotencyRepo.getResponse(req.getRequestId());
    }

    // Perform transfer safely
    debit();
    credit();

    idempotencyRepo.save(req.getRequestId(), SUCCESS);

    return SUCCESS;
}

