Q: What is Idempotency?
A: Same request executed multiple times → same result, no duplicate effect.

2️⃣ Retry Mechanism (Very Important)
❓ Why Retry?

Failures happen due to:

Deadlock

DB timeout

Network glitch

Temporary service failure

✅ Retry Strategy

Retry ONLY for transient failures, NOT for:

Insufficient balance

Validation error

Spring Retry Example
@Retryable(
  value = {DeadlockException.class, TimeoutException.class},
  maxAttempts = 3,
  backoff = @Backoff(delay = 200)
)
public void transferMoney() {
   // transfer logic
}

🔥 Retry Best Practice
Rule	Why
Max retry = 3	Avoid infinite loop
Exponential backoff	Reduce DB pressure
Retry only safe ops	Avoid duplicate
3️⃣ Failure Handling (Real Banking)
Case 1: Service crash after debit

If DB transaction → Rollback → Safe

If distributed (microservices) → Need Saga Pattern

Case 2: Receiver service down

Retry OR queue transaction.

Case 3: Partial Failure

Debit success, credit failed → Use Compensation

Debit A → Fail credit B → Refund A

